Hi Jonathan,

In the newest version (35457)

When I define a delegate graph: DelegateUndirectedGraph<int,  SUndirectedTaggedEdge<int, int>>

I get the error: The type 'SUndirectedTaggedEdge<int,int>' is not compatible with the type 'IEquatable<SUndirectedTaggedEdge<int,int>>'  

This used to compile in 35064. How do I fix it?

 

Thanks,

Vlad
I removed that requirement. Now uses a special edge equality comparer.
